{{Transcript|miniquest}}
{{Transcript list|Kolodion|Chamber guardian}}

==Without level 60 Magic==
* '''Player:''' Hello there. What is this place?
* '''Kolodion:''' Do not waste my time with trivial questions. I am the Great Kolodion, master of battle magic. I have an arena to run.
* '''Player:''' Can I enter?
* '''Kolodion:''' Hah! A wizard of your level? Don't be absurd.
* {{tact|end}}

===Pulling the [[lever (Mage Arena)|Mage Arena lever]] before starting Mage Arena I===
* '''Kolodion:''' You're not allowed in there. Come downstairs if you want to enter my arena.
* {{tact|end}}

==With 60 Magic or higher==
===Introduction===
* '''Player:''' Hello there. What is this place?
* '''Kolodion:''' I am the great Kolodion, master of battle magic, and this is my battle arena. Top wizards travel from all over Gielinor to fight here.
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Can I fight here?}}
** '''Player:''' Can I fight here?
** '''Kolodion:''' My arena is open to any high level wizard, but this is no game. Many wizards fall in this arena, never to rise again. The strongest mages have been destroyed.
** '''Kolodion:''' If you're sure you want in?
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|Yes indeedy.}}
*** '''Player:''' Yes indeedy.
*** '''Kolodion:''' Good, good. You have a healthy sense of competition.
*** '''Kolodion:''' Remember, traveller - in my arena, hand-to-hand combat is useless. Your strength will diminish as you enter the arena, but the spells you can learn are amongst the most powerful in all of Gielinor.
*** '''Kolodion:''' Before I can accept you in, we must duel.
*** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
*** {{topt|Okay, let's fight.}}
**** '''Player:''' Okay, let's fight.
**** '''Kolodion:''' I must first check that you are up to scratch.
**** '''Player:''' You don't need to worry about that.
**** '''Kolodion:''' Not just any magician can enter - only the most powerful and most feared. Before you can use the power of this arena, you must prove yourself against me.
**** {{Qact|The player is teleported to the Mage Arena to fight against Kolodion}}
**** {{tact|end}}
*** {{topt|No thanks.}}
**** '''Player:''' No thanks.
**** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|No I don't.}}
*** '''Player:''' No I don't.
*** '''Kolodion:''' Your loss.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|What's the point of that?}}
** '''Player:''' What's the point of that?
** '''Kolodion:''' We learn how to use our magic to its fullest and how to channel the forces of the cosmos into our world...
** '''Kolodion:''' But mainly, I just like blasting people into dust.
** {{tact|previous}}
* {{topt|That's barbaric!}}
** '''Player:''' That's barbaric!
** '''Kolodion:''' Nope, it's magic. But I know what you mean. So do you want to join us?
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|Yes indeedy.}}
*** {{tact|above}}
** {{topt|No I don't.}}
*** {{tact|above}}

===The duel===
* '''Kolodion:''' {{overhead|You must prove yourself... now!}}
* '''Kolodion (Ogre):''' {{overhead|This is only the beginning; you can't beat me!}}
* '''Kolodion (Spider):''' {{overhead|Foolish mortal; I am unstoppable.}}
* '''Kolodion (Ghost):''' {{overhead|Now you feel it... The dark energy.}}
* '''Kolodion (Black demon):''' {{overhead|Aaaaaaaarrgghhhh! The power!}}
* {{Qact|The player is teleported back to the safe zone after defeating Kolodion's final form}}
* '''Kolodion:''' Well done, young adventurer; you truly are a worthy battle mage.
* '''Player:''' What now?
* '''Kolodion:''' Step into the magic pool. It will take you to a chamber. There, you must decide which god you will represent in the arena.
* '''Player:''' Thanks, Kolodion.
* '''Kolodion:''' That's what I'm here for.
* {{tact|end}}

===Speaking to Kolodion again===
* '''Player:''' Hello, Kolodion.
* '''Kolodion:''' Hello, young mage. You're a tough one.
* '''Player:''' What now?
* {{tact|above}}

==Choosing your god==
===Entering/exiting the chamber===
* {{tbox|You step into the pool of sparkling water. You feel energy rush through your veins.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the chamber guardian===
* '''Player:''' Hello my friend, Kolodion sent me down.
* '''Chamber guardian:''' Sssshhh... the gods are talking. I can hear their whispers.
* '''Chamber guardian:''' Can you hear them adventurer, they're calling you.
* '''Player:''' Erm... ok!
* '''Chamber guardian:''' Go chant at the statue of the god you most wish to represent in this world, you will be rewarded.
* '''Chamber guardian:''' Once you are done, come back to me. I shall supply you with a mage staff ready for battle.
* {{tact|end}}

===Praying at the god statues===
====Guthix====
* {{tbox|You kneel and chant to Guthix...}}
* {{tcond|If the player has 1 inventory space open:}}
** {{tbox|You kneel and chant to Guthix... You feel a rush of energy charge through your veins. Suddenly a cape appears in your pack.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has no inventory spaces open:}}
** {{tbox|You kneel and chant to Guthix... ... but there is no response. You feel that making space in your inventory could help.}}
** {{tact|end}}

====Saradomin====
* {{tbox|You kneel and chant to Saradomin...}}
* {{tcond|If the player has 1 inventory space open:}}
** {{tbox|You kneel and chant to Saradomin... You feel a rush of energy charge through your veins. Suddenly a cape appears in your pack.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has no inventory spaces open:}}
** {{tbox|You kneel and chant to Saradomin... ... but there is no response. You feel that making space in your inventory could help.}}
** {{tact|end}}

====Zamorak====
* {{tbox|You kneel and chant to Zamorak...}}
* {{tcond|If the player has 1 inventory space open:}}
** {{tbox|You kneel and chant to Zamorak... You feel a rush of energy charge through your veins. Suddenly a cape appears in your pack.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has no inventory spaces open:}}
** {{tbox|You kneel and chant to Zamorak... ... but there is no response. You feel that making space in your inventory could help.}}
** {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the chamber guardian after choosing a cape===
* '''Player:''' Hi.
* '''Chamber guardian:''' Hello adventurer, have you made your choice?
* '''Player:''' I have.
* {{tcond|If the player doesn't have the cape with them:}}
** '''Chamber guardian:''' Good, good, I hope you have chosen well. Have you been rewarded with a cape from your chosen god?
** '''Player:''' I'm afraid I don't have it with me.
** '''Chamber guardian:''' Once you have your cape come back to me, and I shall supply you with a mage staff ready for battle.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has the cape with them:}}
** '''Chamber guardian:''' Good, good, I hope you have chosen well. I will now present you with a magic staff. This, along with the cape awarded to you by your chosen god, are all the weapons and armour you will need here.
** {{tcond|If player chose Saradomin cape:}}
*** {{tbox|pic=Saradomin staff detail.png|The guardian hands you an ornate magic staff.}}
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If player chose Guthix cape:}}
*** {{tbox|pic=Guthix staff detail.png|The guardian hands you an ornate magic staff.}}
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If player chose Zamorak cape:}}
*** {{tbox|pic=Zamorak staff detail.png|The guardian hands you an ornate magic staff.}}
*** {{tact|end}}

==Talking to Kolodion after choosing a god==
* '''Player:''' Hello, Kolodion.
* '''Kolodion:''' Hey there, how are you? Are you enjoying the bloodshed?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|I think I've had enough for now.}}
** '''Player:''' I think I've had enough for now.
** '''Kolodion:''' A shame. You're a good battle mage. I hope to see you soon.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|How can I use my new spells outside of the arena?}}
** '''Player:''' How can I use my new spells outside of the arena?
** '''Kolodion:''' Experience, my friend, experience. Once you've used the spell enough times in the arena, you'll be able to use them in the rest of Gielinor.
** '''Player:''' Good stuff.
** '''Kolodion:''' Not so good for the citizens; they won't stand a chance.
** '''Player:''' How am I doing so far?
** {{tcond|If player has cast [[Saradomin Strike]] (unknown) times:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You still need to train with the strike spell inside the arena before you can use it outside.
** {{tcond|If player has cast [[Saradomin Strike]] (unknown) times:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You have completed over half of the training needed to use the strike spell outside of the arena.
** {{tcond|If player has cast [[Saradomin Strike]] (unknown) times:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You are almost ready to use the strike spell outside of the arena.
** {{tcond|If player has cast [[Saradomin Strike]] at least 100 times:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You're experienced enough to use the strike spell anywhere.
** {{tcond|If player has cast [[Claws of Guthix]] (unknown) times:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You still need to train with the claw spell inside the arena before you can use it outside.
** {{tcond|If player has cast [[Claws of Guthix]] (unknown) times:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You have completed over half of the training needed to use the claw spell outside of the arena.
** {{tcond|If player has cast [[Claws of Guthix]] (unknown) times:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You are almost ready to use the claw spell outside of the arena.
** {{tcond|If player has cast [[Claws of Guthix]] at least 100 times:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You're experienced enough to use the claw spell anywhere.
** {{tcond|If player has cast [[Flames of Zamorak]] (unknown) times:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You still need to train with the flame spell inside the arena before you can use it outside.
** {{tcond|If player has cast [[Flames of Zamorak]] (unknown) times:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You have completed over half of the training needed to use the flame spell outside of the arena.
** {{tcond|If player has cast [[Flames of Zamorak]] (unknown) times:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You are almost ready to use the flame spell outside of the arena.
** {{tcond|If player has cast [[Flames of Zamorak]] at least 100 times:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You're experienced enough to use the flame spell anywhere.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Are there any more challenges available?}}
** '''Player:''' Are there any more challenges available?
** {{tcond|If player hasn't mastered all the god spells yet:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You still need to learn how to cast all god spells outside of the arena.
*** '''Kolodion:''' I've made a note of the spells you still need to learn in your journal.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If player doesn't have 75 Magic:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' You have indeed shown potential, [player name].
*** '''Kolodion:''' However, a wizard of your level wouldn't stand a chance.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If player has mastered all the god spells and is 75 Magic:}}
*** '''Kolodion:''' I am one of the most powerful mages in existence. But even my power has limitations. There are some beings however that have power exceeding even my own.
*** {{tact|Continues in [[Transcript:Mage Arena II]]}}
